---
description: Core repository guardrails for the Obsidian MCP project.
alwaysApply: true
---
- Keep the repository markdown-first: vault markdown files are the durable memory source of truth.
- SQLite indexes markdown-derived records for search only; it is not a replacement SSOT store.
- Preserve read-first, write-with-intent behavior and keep markdown writes authoritative.
- Do not hard-code secrets, bearer tokens, vault paths, or private endpoints.
- Reuse existing abstractions, prefer additive evolution, and keep diffs small and reviewable.
- Keep claims tied to checked files, tests, or commands.
- When reporting work, include changed files, commands run, verification status (`pass` / `fail` / `manual`), and remaining risks or assumptions.
